Mike,

For the time being, I'm suggesting we include the following statements =
in the metadata outline. Please condense or revise them as you see fit. =
Note that the vertical accuracy report is similar but not quite =
identical. To complete the quantitative positional attribute fields =
(Accuracy Value and Accuracy Explanation) we can either say that no =
specific value is applicable to the entire data set (explanation: =
confidence intervals will vary with station location and are provided in =
the station shapefile), or we can actually provide the SDUW (square root =
of the UVE) as a metric quantity, identifying it as the scale factor =
used to compute a posteriori confidence regions. Recall that the UVEs =
are already provided in the metadata tables derived from the .DEF files. =
The advantage of entering N/A, or just referring to the shapefiles,  is =
that it doesn't have to change with each data submission.

In the shapefile structure definition, I'll probably use 8.2 numeric =
fields for SD_H/V and SDUW_H/V, and 5-character fields for LOOPS_H/V =
(100,000 loops surely being unlikely). I won't bother you now with the =
details of why I'm suggesting this form for the accuracy assessments. =
Certainly there are other possibilities.

Let me know whether or not this is enough for now. I've been slowly =
digging through some incredibly complex code that I haven't seen in =
about 10 years. I can barely recognize it as something I've written.

--David

